MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: \.worktrees/.+/\.claude/guardrails/
ADVISORY: |
  You are about to write a guardrail rule to a WORKTREE copy
  (.worktrees/*/.claude/guardrails/). Don't.

  Reason: .claude/guardrails/ is gitignored. Rules written in a worktree
  never propagate back to main or to other worktrees — they die when the
  worktree is removed. Future sessions on main will never see the
  guardrail, so the learning is effectively lost.

  This was observed in 2026-04-12: a previous session wrote
  skill-update-needed.md into .worktrees/arcade-batch-2/.claude/guardrails/
  and the advisory sat unread until a completely unrelated session in
  the main checkout happened to surface it — by which time the context
  was stale.

  How to apply: redirect the write to the MAIN repo path:
    /Users/manu/Projects/pecking-order/.claude/guardrails/<rule-name>.rule

  Applies equally to skill-update-needed.md, finite-*.rule, broad-*.rule,
  and any other file under .claude/guardrails/.
